                        <p><strong>Changing Memoization to Tabulation</strong></p>
<p>To switch from storing answers during recursion (memoization) to filling them directly in a table (tabulation), we make a table of the same size and set all values to 0 at the start.</p>
<p>First, we set up the starting conditions just like we did in the recursive method.</p>
<ul>
  <li>For the first item: If it fits in the bag, we put its value in the table. This is done using a simple loop.</li>
  <li>After filling the first row, we move through the table row by row. The outer loop goes through each item, and the inner loop goes through each possible weight limit.</li>
  <li>For each cell, we use the same logic as before: check if skipping or taking the item gives a better total value, and fill the cell with the best one.</li>
  <li>After filling the whole table, the last cell in the bottom-right corner gives us the final answer.</li>
